<concept xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:ditabase.xsd" id="i20170523060333956" status="new">
   <title id="title">Style guide</title>
   <abstract id="abstract">A style guide provides <shortdesc id="shortdesc">a set of guidelines for writing and designing documents</shortdesc>. Guidelines are key to implementing efficient collaborative authoring practices and reuse strategies.</abstract>
   <prolog id="prolog">
      <author id="author">France Baril</author>
      <publisher id="publisher">Architextus</publisher>
      <critdates id="critdates">
         <created id="created" date="2017-05-23"/>
      </critdates>
   </prolog>
   <conbody id="body"><p id="a0">The purpose of guidelines is to:</p><ul id="a1">
         <li id="a2"><keypoint id="a3">Improve consistency</keypoint> within and across documents</li>
         <li id="a4"><keypoint id="a5">Enforce best practices</keypoint></li>
         <li id="a6"><keypoint id="a7">Improve compliance</keypoint>, for those in regulated industries</li>
      </ul>
      <p id="a8">In the case of DITA the guidelines also:</p>
      <ul id="a9">
         <li id="a10">Support collaborative practices</li>
         <li id="a11">Optimize reuse opportunities</li>
      </ul>
      <p id="a12">Benefits are:</p>
      <ul id="a13">
         <li id="a14">Better user experience</li>
         <li id="a15">Lower content creation costs</li>
         <li id="a16">Lower translation costs</li>
         <li id="a17">Faster time to market</li>
      </ul>
   </conbody>
</concept>